The letters from @Lakers/MSG personnel discussing the @laclippers proposed arena in Inglewood is fascinating reading, not because of the BTS look at the organization, but the attitude shown by Buss & others: Dismissiveness and Arrogance.

We’ve seen evidence of Lakers overconfidence before. Whether it be the Lamarcus Aldridge fiasco, or the more embarrassing failure with Davis, this same attitude is seen in the emails. They arrogantly brand Ballmer’s plans a failure without thought...

Lakers fans have been dismissive of the Clippers forever, especially this year. When Lakers fans read reports praising the Clippers and their future, the response is “ringzzz,” which doesn’t address the Lakers struggles today. This attitude permeates the team operations as well.

Not taking a rival seriously, especially one with deep pockets/great personnel, is a doomed business strategy. The Clippers will likely never threaten Lakers legacy, but they are a threat to their basketball ops presently and biz ops in the future.

The attitude on display in those emails is not one that builds confidence. That Lakers fans don’t see this as a precarious position is remarkably short sighted. Constantly invoking the past to prop up a dismal present, with a 50/50 future outlook at doesn’t bring championships.

It’s not all without hope for the Lakers - as long as they can develop this young core the future looks interesting, but considering how many good players they’ve traded recently (Hello, Zubac!), my confidence in their talent assessment is low.
